in purgatory?

52:42.594 --> 52:44.117
I just need a night to myself.

52:44.161 --> 52:46.337
-So do you.
-Don't tell me what I need.

52:46.380 --> 52:48.034
A night by yourself.

52:48.077 --> 52:50.036
Yes, Theo, I get it--
by myself.

52:50.079 --> 52:52.560
Max is not here.
He has never been here.

52:52.604 --> 52:55.346
Oh, right, 'cause of all
the big meetings in New York.

52:55.389 --> 52:57.130
Can I get in, please?

52:57.174 --> 53:00.089
Hey, listen, um,
you know, I want to take back

53:00.133 --> 53:03.092
that "fuck you all night"
thing I said.

53:03.136 --> 53:05.138
-Yeah, whatever.
-Yeah, let me be clear--

53:05.182 --> 53:07.053
I don't actually care
who fucks you all night.

53:07.096 --> 53:09.316
-Oh, my God. Jesus.
-I'm sure it's quite a list.

53:13.929 --> 53:16.410
-Drive safe, sweetie.

53:25.114 --> 53:28.205
Hey, do you have
both your phones?

54:24.870 --> 54:26.915
THEO: They didn't have
any peanut butter.

54:26.959 --> 54:29.222
-ELLA: Why not?
-THEO: It's not a thing here.

54:29.266 --> 54:32.094
-So, what's that stuff?
-I don't know.

54:32.138 --> 54:34.967
Starts with L.
Well, two L's, actually.

54:35.010 --> 54:37.012
I don't want it.

54:39.406 --> 54:41.843
-It's pretty good.
-No, it isn't.

54:41.887 --> 54:43.802
Okay, it's not pretty good.

54:43.845 --> 54:45.499
It tastes kind of weird.

54:45.543 --> 54:49.198
But it's not poison,
and it's what we have.

54:49.242 --> 54:51.288
-I'm not eating it.
-Could you please

54:51.331 --> 54:53.681
just stop with the scooter
for one second, honey?

54:53.725 --> 54:56.162
So you might as well just

54:56.205 --> 54:58.817
throw it in
the garbage can for me

54:58.860 --> 55:00.514
because I'm just not
gonna eat it.

55:00.558 --> 55:03.169
Honey, could you please
get off the scooter?

55:04.170 --> 55:06.346
-I'm sorry.

55:06.390 --> 55:08.000
Sorry.

55:08.043 --> 55:09.610
It's okay. It's okay.

55:09.654 --> 55:12.352
Honey, it's okay.

55:19.751 --> 55:21.622
I don't like it here.

55:23.058 --> 55:24.669
I don't think I do, either.

55:24.712 --> 55:28.542
I have weird dreams,
and I get in bad moods.

55:28.586 --> 55:30.065
Me, too.

55:30.109 --> 55:33.155
Did you and Mommy have a fight?

55:36.420 --> 55:37.986
Yeah.

55:38.030 --> 55:40.859
Today is a terrible day.

55:40.902 --> 55:43.514
-I want to go home.
-So do I.

55:43.557 --> 55:46.908
As soon as Mom gets back
with the car, okay?

55:46.952 --> 55:49.563
-When will that be?
-Tomorrow.

56:00.661 --> 56:02.402
Hmm.

56:07.886 --> 56:09.583
Huh.

56:14.458 --> 56:16.634
-What are you doing?
-Experiment.

56:16.677 --> 56:20.289
-What kind of experiment?
-Water experiment.

56:32.389 --> 56:34.391
That's freaky.

56:34.434 --> 56:35.609
I'll say.

56:41.659 --> 56:43.400
What's that?

56:43.443 --> 56:44.662
It's a triangle.

56:44.705 --> 56:46.403
I'm checking the angles.

56:46.446 --> 56:48.492
Why you want to check angles?

56:48.535 --> 56:51.016
These are all very
heads-up questions, honey.

56:55.760 --> 56:57.979
Huh.

57:00.460 --> 57:02.593
Does this wall
look right to you?

57:02.636 --> 57:04.464
Um...

57:04.508 --> 57:08.294
it looks like a wall to me.

57:08.337 --> 57:10.688
Can't tell from in here.

57:17.172 --> 57:20.132
What are you looking for?

57:20.175 --> 57:22.395
I don't know.

57:23.222 --> 57:24.789
ELLA:
16, seven,

57:24.832 --> 57:26.791
12, zero.

57:26.834 --> 57:28.140
Honey, honey, honey.

57:28.183 --> 57:29.881
-You taught me that.

57:29.924 --> 57:32.927
16! 17! 18!

57:32.971 --> 57:34.625
-Okay, you got me.
-One!

57:34.668 --> 57:36.191
Yay!

57:41.936 --> 57:44.025
-Hang on tight, honey.
-Okay.

57:45.679 --> 57:48.116
-Don't let go.
-Okay.

57:51.511 --> 57:53.208
26 feet.

57:53.252 --> 57:55.472
-Hold on tight.
-Okay.

58:01.782 --> 58:03.480
21.

58:04.350 --> 58:05.786
Are you at the corner?

58:05.830 --> 58:07.440
-Yeah.
-You sure?

58:07.484 --> 58:08.615
Yeah.

58:08.659 --> 58:09.703
You can let go.

58:10.748 --> 58:12.445
What does it say?

58:12.489 --> 58:16.014
Says this room is
five feet longer on the inside

58:16.057 --> 58:18.103
than it is on the outside.

58:20.366 --> 58:22.716
Wait. How does that work?

58:24.065 --> 58:25.763
It doesn't.

58:25.806 --> 58:27.199
I'm cold.

58:27.242 --> 58:28.722
Get your coat on, hon.

58:28.766 --> 58:30.158
Okay.

59:08.632 --> 59:10.285
Ella?

59:12.940 --> 59:14.551
Ella.

59:21.993 --> 59:23.777
Ella.

59:27.781 --> 59:30.871
So not in the mood
for hide-and-seek.

59:34.092 --> 59:36.137
Ella!

59:43.667 --> 59:45.407
Ella.

59:47.888 --> 59:49.890
I give up, honey.

59:49.934 --> 59:51.457
You win.

59:51.500 --> 59:53.372
Ella.

59:59.552 --> 1:00:01.206
Ella?

1:00:12.304 --> 1:00:13.914
Okay, Ella, it's not funny.

1:00:13.958 --> 1:00:15.655
Come out, please.

1:00:17.265 --> 1:00:18.919
ELLA:
Baba?

1:00:25.883 --> 1:00:27.624
Baba.

1:00:31.715 --> 1:00:33.455
Ella.

1:00:45.729 --> 1:00:47.513
What the hell?

1:01:14.496 --> 1:01:16.498
ELLA :
Baba?

1:01:18.196 --> 1:01:20.241
Are you there?

1:01:27.988 --> 1:01:29.555
Baba?

1:01:44.570 --> 1:01:46.354
Ella?

1:01:59.628 --> 1:02:01.369
Oh, God.

1:02:21.825 --> 1:02:23.652
Hello?

1:02:26.655 --> 1:02:29.310
Is anybody down here?

1:02:34.011 --> 1:02:36.230
I got lost.

1:02:52.333 --> 1:02:54.509
Hello?

1:03:00.124 --> 1:03:01.821
Who are you?

1:03:06.739 --> 1:03:08.523
Can you hear me?

1:03:10.047 --> 1:03:12.397
Are you okay?

1:03:17.837 --> 1:03:19.491
Ella.

1:03:23.147 --> 1:03:26.803
What an innocent face.

1:03:29.588 --> 1:03:31.895
We don't get that much here.

1:03:32.939 --> 1:03:34.288
Such a lucky daddy.

1:03:34.332 --> 1:03:38.205
I bet you'd stay with him
forever, wouldn't you?

1:03:44.429 --> 1:03:46.692
-Ella!
-ELLA: Baba!

1:03:49.913 --> 1:03:53.220
-Daddy, where are you?

1:03:53.264 --> 1:03:54.874
Ella?

1:03:54.918 --> 1:03:57.137
-Ella!
-Baba, I'm scared.

1:03:57.181 --> 1:03:58.312
Stay back from the door!

1:03:59.618 --> 1:04:01.838
Baba, please, please.

1:04:01.881 --> 1:04:03.100
Baba!

1:04:06.973 --> 1:04:09.106
Oh, Jesus.

1:04:09.149 --> 1:04:11.412
Ella. Honey, are you okay?

1:04:11.456 --> 1:04:14.024
-I got... I got lost.
-Oh, baby.

1:04:14.067 --> 1:04:15.503
I got lost in the house.

1:04:15.547 --> 1:04:17.070
I know. I know.
I got you now.

1:04:17.114 --> 1:04:18.985
-I was looking for you
everywhere. -I know.

1:04:19.029 --> 1:04:20.944
I know, my love.
It's okay. It's okay.

1:04:20.987 --> 1:04:23.076
-I was scared.
-I know. I know.

1:04:23.120 --> 1:04:25.383
-I got you.
-I couldn't find you.

1:04:25.426 --> 1:04:27.037
I got you now.

1:04:30.649 --> 1:04:33.173
You're okay now.
All right?

1:04:33.217 --> 1:04:37.569
You and me, we're not getting
out of each other's sight again.

1:04:37.612 --> 1:04:39.353
All right?
That's a deal.

1:04:39.397 --> 1:04:41.181
I want to go home.

1:04:42.226 --> 1:04:43.314
We will.

1:04:43.357 --> 1:04:45.403
-Promise?
-Yeah. Yep.

1:04:45.446 --> 1:04:47.492
Yeah. I promise.

1:04:47.535 --> 1:04:49.189
-I'm just gonna call...
-Wait!

1:04:49.233 --> 1:04:51.757
Okay, I'm not going anywhere.
I'm just gonna call your mom,

1:04:51.800 --> 1:04:53.498
and she's gonna come right now,

1:04:53.541 --> 1:04:56.196
and she's gonna pick us up,
okay?

1:04:58.372 --> 1:04:59.591
SUSANNA :
Hey, it's me.

1:04:59.634 --> 1:05:01.114
Um, leave me a message.

1:05:02.507 --> 1:05:04.988
Her phone is off
or she's out of range.

1:05:05.031 --> 1:05:07.599
Why don't you call
her other phone?

1:05:10.689 --> 1:05:13.735
Uh... I don't have that number.

1:05:14.780 --> 1:05:16.695
Oh.

1:05:16.738 --> 1:05:19.480
All right,
I-I'm gonna try her again.

1:05:20.917 --> 1:05:23.745
Hey, it's me.
Um, leave me a message.

1:05:23.789 --> 1:05:26.226
THEO:
Hey, uh, it's me.

1:05:26.270 --> 1:05:28.141
Call me when you get this,

1:05:28.185 --> 1:05:30.230
as soon as you get it.

1:05:33.146 --> 1:05:35.757
Uh, okay.

1:05:35.801 --> 1:05:38.499
This is not a problem.

1:05:38.543 --> 1:05:40.762
ELLA:
Okay.

1:05:42.851 --> 1:05:45.942
All right, yeah, it's a...
it's a little bit of a problem.

1:05:48.118 --> 1:05:50.076
But I got an idea.

1:05:50.120 --> 1:05:51.556
Aha!

1:05:51.599 --> 1:05:53.123
All right.

1:05:53.166 --> 1:05:54.428
We are out of here.

1:05:54.472 --> 1:05:57.214
We are so out of here.

1:06:07.702 --> 1:06:08.877
They don't answer?

1:06:08.921 --> 1:06:10.401
Uh, just give him a minute.

1:06:10.444 --> 1:06:12.272
This guy's kind of slow.

1:06:21.064 --> 1:06:22.021
Hello.

1:06:22.065 --> 1:06:24.284
Hello. Hi.
Uh, this is Theo Conroy.

1:06:24.328 --> 1:06:25.851
I was in the other day.

1:06:25.894 --> 1:06:29.420
Uh, we-we rented the house
u-up the hill.

1:06:29.463 --> 1:06:30.943
Where?

1:06:30.987 --> 1:06:32.553
Stetler. The Stetler house.

1:06:32.597 --> 1:06:34.294
We rented Stetler's house.

1:06:34.338 --> 1:06:36.296
I remember.

1:06:36.340 --> 1:06:38.864
-We need a taxi.
-A what?

1:06:38.907 --> 1:06:40.083
A taxi.

1:06:40.126 --> 1:06:42.737
W-We need somebody
to come pick us up.

1:06:42.781 --> 1:06:45.088
There are no taxis around here.

1:06:45.131 --> 1:06:46.350
Well, where, then?

1:06:46.393 --> 1:06:47.742
Marlborough Inn, maybe.

1:06:47.786 --> 1:06:49.179
Unless he's still on holiday.

1:06:49.222 --> 1:06:52.573
Okay, uh, could you give me
that number, please?

1:06:53.400 --> 1:06:54.836
Hello?

1:06:54.880 --> 1:06:57.970
Did you try the triangle?

1:07:00.799 --> 1:07:02.496
THEO :
Yes.

1:07:02.540 --> 1:07:04.542
I tried the triangle.

1:07:04.585 --> 1:07:07.327
They never fit
the angles up there.

1:07:07.371 --> 1:07:09.112
Why not?

1:07:09.155 --> 1:07:10.983
What is this place?

1:07:11.027 --> 1:07:13.899
Somebody from here, Hans Eagly,

1:07:13.942 --> 1:07:15.988
he owns the Lindenhof.

1:07:16.032 --> 1:07:20.297
He said an ant doesn't know
what a cathedral is

1:07:20.340 --> 1:07:23.648
or a power plant or a volcano.

1:07:23.691 --> 1:07:26.607
It's the same with that house.

1:07:26.651 --> 1:07:29.654
You don't know
what you can't know.

1:07:31.743 --> 1:07:33.397
Are you still there?

1:07:33.440 --> 1:07:34.746
We need a taxi now.

1:07:34.789 --> 1:07:36.269
Don't shout at me.

1:07:36.313 --> 1:07:37.836
I'm not... shouting.

1:07:37.879 --> 1:07:40.578
There was a different house
before that one.

1:07:40.621 --> 1:07:42.580
What sort of house?

1:07:42.623 --> 1:07:44.364
Just different.

1:07:44.408 --> 1:07:47.280
And before that, a tower.

1:07:47.324 --> 1:07:48.412
Tower?

1:07:48.455 --> 1:07:50.327
It's a legend.

1:07:50.370 --> 1:07:54.374
The Devil builds a tower
to collect souls,

1:07:54.418 --> 1:07:56.637
and God destroys it.

1:07:56.681 --> 1:08:01.164
But the Devil just builds it up
again and again.

1:08:01.207 --> 1:08:04.602
People have always stayed
in that house.

1:08:04.645 --> 1:08:06.125
Some don't leave.

1:08:06.169 --> 1:08:08.780
The right ones
usually find the place.

1:08:08.823 --> 1:08:11.261
Or perhaps it's
the other way around.

1:08:11.304 --> 1:08:13.393
The place finds them.

1:08:13.437 --> 1:08:15.265
We need to leave now.

1:08:16.527 --> 1:08:18.485
That's not up to me.

1:08:18.529 --> 1:08:20.357
-Hello?

1:08:20.400 --> 1:08:21.358
Hello!

1:08:21.401 --> 1:08:23.621
STETLER:
I'm here.

1:08:23.664 --> 1:08:26.145
I'm always here.

1:08:31.977 --> 1:08:33.935
-How far is the village?
-It's pretty far.

1:08:33.979 --> 1:08:36.155
It's about four miles.

1:08:36.199 --> 1:08:37.461
But it's dark.

1:08:37.504 --> 1:08:39.637
-Yep.
-And cold.

1:08:39.680 --> 1:08:41.421
Would you rather stay here?

1:08:41.465 --> 1:08:43.858
-No.
-Me, neither.

1:08:45.164 --> 1:08:47.210
-But what about our stuff?
-We'll get new stuff.

1:08:50.430 --> 1:08:51.866
Oh, no.

1:08:53.694 --> 1:08:55.696
Why don't you unlock the door?

1:09:08.448 --> 1:09:10.624
ELLA:
Are you sure you know the way?

1:09:10.668 --> 1:09:13.192
THEO:
Yep. Just one road,

1:09:13.236 --> 1:09:15.760
right down straight into town.

1:09:21.244 --> 1:09:23.463
ELLA : There's
somebody inside the house.

1:09:29.382 --> 1:09:30.470
Okay, up.

1:09:31.689 --> 1:09:33.212
Baba, what's happening?

1:09:33.256 --> 1:09:34.735
Let's go.

1:09:42.874 --> 1:09:44.832
-ELLA: I'm cold.
-THEO: I know.

1:09:44.876 --> 1:09:47.357
THEO:
It's cold, but we're okay.

1:09:47.400 --> 1:09:48.793
ELLA:
I can walk.

1:09:48.836 --> 1:09:50.882
THEO:
I got you, honey. I got you.

1:09:53.493 --> 1:09:55.756
ELLA:
It's freezing.

1:09:55.800 --> 1:09:58.194
THEO:
Hey. You're doing great.

1:10:01.806 --> 1:10:03.286
Honey, I-I got to
put you down, okay?

1:10:03.329 --> 1:10:04.939
-ELLA: Okay.

1:10:09.074 --> 1:10:10.771
Are you sure you know
where we're going?

1:10:10.815 --> 1:10:14.166
Yeah. Just one road,
right into town.

1:10:17.125 --> 1:10:19.345
-ELLA: What was that?

1:10:24.176 --> 1:10:25.873
-What was that?
-Uh, it was nothing, honey.

1:10:25.917 --> 1:10:27.092
It was just an animal, animal.

1:10:27.135 --> 1:10:29.747
-Okay.
-Just a-a deer, something.

1:10:29.790 --> 1:10:31.575
Okay, up you go.

1:10:46.807 --> 1:10:48.722
THEO:
Almost there, honey.

1:10:48.766 --> 1:10:50.246
Not much further.

1:10:50.289 --> 1:10:53.161
ELLA:
I can't... I can't feel my toes.

1:10:53.205 --> 1:10:55.251
THEO:
Maybe they'll have a fire.

1:10:58.036 --> 1:11:01.082
ELLA: I've never been
this c-cold before.

1:11:01.126 --> 1:11:03.215
THEO:
You never lived in Chicago.

1:11:03.259 --> 1:11:05.043
ELLA:
How much farther is it?

1:11:05.086 --> 1:11:07.306
THEO:
I'm starting to see lights.

1:11:07.350 --> 1:11:09.439
ELLA:
It's... cold.

1:11:09.482 --> 1:11:10.875
Yeah.

1:11:12.355 --> 1:11:14.835
I'm definitely seeing
some lights.

1:11:17.925 --> 1:11:19.710
We made it.

1:11:21.973 --> 1:11:23.801
We did it.

1:11:23.844 --> 1:11:25.846
We did it, honey.

1:11:25.890 --> 1:11:28.196
We're there.

1:11:28.240 --> 1:11:29.807
We're...

1:11:34.028 --> 1:11:36.161
We're back.

1:11:36.204 --> 1:11:38.206
What?

1:11:44.561 --> 1:11:45.649
We're back.

1:11:45.692 --> 1:11:46.867
But...

1:11:46.911 --> 1:11:50.088
But we were going down
the whole time.

1:11:50.131 --> 1:11:52.003
THEO: I'll explain it to you
in the morning.

1:11:52.046 --> 1:11:54.353
- It's complicated.
-No, it isn't.

1:11:54.397 --> 1:11:58.183
We were walking d-down
the whole time.

1:11:58.226 --> 1:12:00.490
I don't want to go in there.

1:12:00.533 --> 1:12:01.926
We don't have a choice.

1:12:01.969 --> 1:12:03.449
I'm not going in there.

1:12:03.493 --> 1:12:06.234
-Honey...
-I hate that house!

1:12:06.278 --> 1:12:09.020
-It's too cold out here, honey.
-No. No!

1:12:09.063 --> 1:12:12.284
Your mom's gonna be here
in the morning with the car.

1:12:12.328 --> 1:12:13.938
Please don't make me
go in there.

1:12:15.766 --> 1:12:17.985
Listen to me.

1:12:19.813 --> 1:12:22.990
We would not make it out here.

1:12:23.034 --> 1:12:25.166
Not all night.

1:12:25.210 --> 1:12:27.386
Do you understand
what I'm saying to you?

1:12:30.563 --> 1:12:33.523
I will protect you.

1:12:33.566 --> 1:12:35.655
I'm gonna make sure...

1:12:35.699 --> 1:12:38.136
that nothing happens to you.

1:12:38.179 --> 1:12:40.704
I'm gonna protect you.

1:12:40.747 --> 1:12:43.097
Okay? Do you trust me?

1:12:43.141 --> 1:12:45.665
I-I trust you.

1:12:45.709 --> 1:12:47.667
One more night.

1:12:47.711 --> 1:12:49.539
Just one more night.

1:12:49.582 --> 1:12:50.888
We can do it.

1:12:50.931 --> 1:12:53.673
Okay?
Let's go. Let's go.

1:13:09.080 --> 1:13:10.908
THEO:
Okay? Feeling better?

1:13:10.951 --> 1:13:12.692
It's warm now, right?

1:13:12.736 --> 1:13:14.172
I'm not going anywhere.

1:13:14.215 --> 1:13:16.957
Just try and get some sleep,
honey.

1:13:17.784 --> 1:13:19.133
Daddy?

1:13:19.177 --> 1:13:20.613
Yes, my love.

1:13:20.657 --> 1:13:22.398
You still love Mommy?

1:13:22.441 --> 1:13:23.703
Yeah.

1:13:23.747 --> 1:13:25.488
I do.

1:13:25.531 --> 1:13:27.751
But not enough?

1:13:27.794 --> 1:13:30.667
Well, s-sweetie, uh...

1:13:30.710 --> 1:13:34.714
I never really deserved
to have your mom.

1:13:34.758 --> 1:13:37.630
What about me?

1:13:39.023 --> 1:13:40.285
What about you?

1:13:40.328 --> 1:13:43.114
Do you love me enough?

1:13:44.898 --> 1:13:47.466
Aw.

1:13:47.510 --> 1:13:49.729
You know...

1:13:49.773 --> 1:13:51.514
when I was young...

1:13:51.557 --> 1:13:55.692
things came pretty easy for me,

1:13:55.735 --> 1:13:58.129
and-and-and really quick, like,

1:13:58.172 --> 1:14:00.044
-success and money.

1:14:00.087 --> 1:14:01.741
Stuff like that.

1:14:01.785 --> 1:14:03.743
And I think I...

1:14:03.787 --> 1:14:05.919
I kind of lost track

1:14:05.963 --> 1:14:09.662
of who I was, you know, and...

1:14:09.706 --> 1:14:14.885
I became someone that
I wasn't really proud of.

1:14:14.928 --> 1:14:17.409
Everything in my life just...

1:14:17.453 --> 1:14:21.500
just came too easy
and too quick.

1:14:23.023 --> 1:14:24.982
Except for you.

1:14:25.025 --> 1:14:28.551
The one thing that mattered.

1:14:28.594 --> 1:14:30.944
For you, I had to wait.

1:14:30.988 --> 1:14:33.860
Until you were old?

1:14:35.296 --> 1:14:37.429
Hey, lady, I'm not that old.

1:14:41.912 --> 1:14:46.090
I love you much more
than enough.

1:14:46.133 --> 1:14:49.049
I love you, Baba.

1:15:46.629 --> 1:15:48.152
Ella!

1:15:56.639 --> 1:15:58.118
Ella. Ella!

1:15:58.162 --> 1:16:00.599
ELLA :
Baba!

1:16:01.905 --> 1:16:03.297
THEO:
Ella?

1:16:05.909 --> 1:16:07.563
Ella.

1:17:05.708 --> 1:17:07.274
Ella!

1:17:20.244 --> 1:17:22.376
Ella!

1:18:18.302 --> 1:18:19.956
-THEO: Wow.

1:18:19.999 --> 1:18:21.392
Seems bigger on the inside.

1:18:21.435 --> 1:18:23.220
-Oh, my God.
-Way bigger.

1:18:23.263 --> 1:18:25.004
Oh, I love it.

1:18:25.048 --> 1:18:26.745
There's no service, though.

1:18:26.789 --> 1:18:28.660
-THEO: You hear that?
-Hey!

1:18:28.704 --> 1:18:29.530
What?

1:18:29.574 --> 1:18:31.619
-Hey!
-The quiet.

1:18:31.663 --> 1:18:33.883
-ELLA: Baba!

1:18:35.275 --> 1:18:36.581
Hello.

1:18:36.624 --> 1:18:39.758
STETLER:
You're not going anywhere.

1:18:43.936 --> 1:18:45.764
THEO:
Hey, I'm back.

1:18:47.070 --> 1:18:48.419
Hey.

1:18:48.462 --> 1:18:50.029
ELLA: Sorry that
happened to you, Baba.

1:18:52.249 --> 1:18:54.730
ELLA:
Does everyone go to Heaven?

1:18:56.819 --> 1:18:59.212
THEO :
That's what they say.

1:18:59.256 --> 1:19:01.737
Where are you?

1:19:04.130 --> 1:19:07.394
Oh, my God, Ella,
you have to come up here.

1:19:07.438 --> 1:19:09.309
Your bed is the size of...

1:19:38.904 --> 1:19:40.297
Ella.

1:19:42.908 --> 1:19:44.605
Ella.

1:19:47.695 --> 1:19:49.132
Ella.

1:19:49.175 --> 1:19:51.221
Where are you?

1:20:01.797 --> 1:20:03.842
Susanna?

1:20:03.886 --> 1:20:06.018
-Susanna!

1:20:12.024 --> 1:20:13.504
THEO:
Wow.

1:20:13.547 --> 1:20:14.635
Seems bigger on the inside.

1:20:14.679 --> 1:20:15.985
-Oh, my God.
-Way bigger.

1:20:27.170 --> 1:20:29.259
Your name Stetler?

1:20:29.302 --> 1:20:31.914
I got a lot of names.

1:20:31.957 --> 1:20:33.437
Where's Ella?

1:20:33.480 --> 1:20:36.222
A lot of faces.

1:20:36.266 --> 1:20:38.485
And a lot of houses.

1:20:38.529 --> 1:20:41.706
Been a room here for you
for a long time.

1:20:41.749 --> 1:20:44.100
-Where is she?
-Where you belong.

1:20:44.143 --> 1:20:46.319
With me.

1:20:46.363 --> 1:20:47.712
ELLA:
Baba!

1:20:47.755 --> 1:20:49.409
In here!

1:20:49.453 --> 1:20:51.672
Baba, I'm scared! I'm here!

1:20:51.716 --> 1:20:55.546
-Ella! Ella!
-Please find me. Please find me.

1:20:55.589 --> 1:20:56.808
Ella. Ella.

1:20:56.852 --> 1:20:59.245
ELLA:
It's hot in here!

1:20:59.289 --> 1:21:01.160
Let her go.

1:21:01.204 --> 1:21:02.814
Such a lucky daddy.

1:21:03.728 --> 1:21:05.382
She would do anything for you.

1:21:05.425 --> 1:21:07.906
Let her go, you son of a bitch.

1:21:07.950 --> 1:21:09.995
She'd even stay.

1:21:11.954 --> 1:21:13.912
Let her go. Let her go!

1:21:13.956 --> 1:21:15.044
Think of it.

1:21:15.087 --> 1:21:17.568
Together forever.

1:21:17.611 --> 1:21:20.049
Just you and her...

1:21:20.092 --> 1:21:22.138
and a lie.

1:21:22.181 --> 1:21:23.574
She's innocent.

1:21:23.617 --> 1:21:25.228
Sure she is.

1:21:25.271 --> 1:21:27.273
But she's with you.

1:21:27.317 --> 1:21:28.971
I didn't do it!

1:21:29.580 --> 1:21:31.060
I didn't do it!

1:21:31.103 --> 1:21:33.540
ELLA:
Daddy, I don't know where I am!

1:21:33.584 --> 1:21:35.803
Baba, please, please!

1:21:36.500 --> 1:21:38.632
Let her go!

1:21:47.641 --> 1:21:49.208
The sins of the fathers...

1:21:49.252 --> 1:21:50.949
I didn't do it!

1:21:54.387 --> 1:21:56.215
...come down on the kids.

1:21:56.259 --> 1:21:58.435
But I... didn't...

1:21:58.478 --> 1:21:59.871
do it!

1:22:03.309 --> 1:22:06.530
That's the problem with mirrors.

1:22:08.575 --> 1:22:11.665
They always show you yourself.

1:22:20.152 --> 1:22:22.024
Please.

1:22:22.067 --> 1:22:24.287
Please let her go.
Please let her go.

1:22:24.330 --> 1:22:25.810
Please, please, please, please.

1:22:25.853 --> 1:22:27.768
Me?

1:22:27.812 --> 1:22:30.858
The only one
keeping her here is you.

1:22:35.689 --> 1:22:37.300
I can't do it.

1:22:37.343 --> 1:22:39.171
I can't do this.

1:22:40.303 --> 1:22:41.608
I can't do this.

1:22:41.652 --> 1:22:43.001
I can't do it anymore.

1:22:43.045 --> 1:22:44.307
I can't.

1:22:44.350 --> 1:22:46.700
I can't do this.
I-I can't do it.

1:22:46.744 --> 1:22:48.833
I can't do this.

1:22:52.445 --> 1:22:56.580
Then you know what
you've got to do, don't you?

1:23:02.325 --> 1:23:03.935
ELLA:
Baba?

1:23:05.458 --> 1:23:07.112
Oh... Ella.

1:23:07.156 --> 1:23:08.766
Oh, honey.

1:23:10.202 --> 1:23:12.030
Oh, I am so sorry.

1:23:12.074 --> 1:23:14.511
Ella, I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

1:23:14.554 --> 1:23:16.556
What for?

1:23:18.384 --> 1:23:20.343
For...

1:23:20.386 --> 1:23:22.736
not being what you think I am.

1:23:22.780 --> 1:23:25.826
But... I love you
no matter what.

1:23:25.870 --> 1:23:28.873
Don't you know that yet?

1:23:38.317 --> 1:23:39.971
Is it time to go home?

1:23:48.849 --> 1:23:51.156
It is, for you and Mommy.

1:23:57.075 --> 1:23:58.685
Come on.

1:24:19.271 --> 1:24:21.012
Hi, Mommy.

1:25:06.318 --> 1:25:08.277
Where is her stuff?

1:25:08.320 --> 1:25:10.888
I'll send it. Later.

1:25:13.847 --> 1:25:16.676
You're not coming with us?

1:25:17.634 --> 1:25:19.940
It'll never let me.

1:25:19.984 --> 1:25:21.855
I'd end up right back here.

1:25:21.899 --> 1:25:24.467
And if you were with me,
you would, too.

1:25:24.510 --> 1:25:26.164
I belong here.

1:25:26.208 --> 1:25:30.037
Can we just try
and work through it?

1:25:31.517 --> 1:25:32.997
I love you.

1:25:33.040 --> 1:25:35.173
I love you so much.

1:25:36.653 --> 1:25:38.394
But...

1:25:38.437 --> 1:25:40.613
I always knew that
you were only borrowed.

1:25:40.657 --> 1:25:43.703
Stop talking crazy.

1:25:44.704 --> 1:25:46.793
Just get in the car,

1:25:46.837 --> 1:25:49.448
and we can talk about it.

1:25:49.492 --> 1:25:51.842
I killed her, Suse.

1:25:58.544 --> 1:26:00.720
I let her drown.

1:26:04.202 --> 1:26:06.465
I could've pulled her out,

1:26:06.509 --> 1:26:08.337
and I didn't.

1:26:11.383 --> 1:26:13.080
I watched her die.

1:26:15.213 --> 1:26:18.869
All those years being so angry,

1:26:18.912 --> 1:26:22.699
hating her so much, and...

1:26:22.742 --> 1:26:24.962
keeping it inside.

1:26:26.355 --> 1:26:28.748
I should've left...

1:26:29.575 --> 1:26:31.882
...years before.

1:26:32.926 --> 1:26:34.885
But I didn't.

1:26:40.412 --> 1:26:42.371
I belong...

1:26:42.414 --> 1:26:44.155
right here.

1:26:49.204 --> 1:26:51.989
Can't run away from your shadow.

1:26:57.255 --> 1:27:01.041
ELLA : There's
somebody inside the house.

1:27:06.656 --> 1:27:08.397
Baba, what's happening?

1:27:08.440 --> 1:27:10.181
THEO:
Let's go.

1:27:19.712 --> 1:27:23.150
SHOPKEEPER: People have always
stayed in that house.

1:27:23.194 --> 1:27:26.241
Some don't leave.

1:27:26.284 --> 1:27:29.592
The right ones
usually find the place.

1:27:29.635 --> 1:27:32.029
Or maybe it's
the other way around.

1:27:34.118 --> 1:27:36.207
The place finds them.

